dcterms:description: The SPDR S&P 500 ETF (SPY), also known as the SPY ETF, is an Exchange-Traded Fund (ETF) that tracks the performance of the S&P 500. Like S&P, SPY provides the diversification of a mutual fund, the flexibility of a stock and lower trading fees.
